Description: Egypt, statue of adult male leader/ruler, Ramesses, standing between two stone columns. Relief carvings [hieroglyphs?] on statue and columns. Ruined temple site, Luxor. Medium: Gelatin silver print.
Producer name: Photographed by: John Frederick Clifford Hunt
